cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and discourse analysis. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses neural networks to model inter-dependencies between discourse units. Additionally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for classification. Finally, it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with predicting discourse relations in a paragraph.
